.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Identifier \- Mapping Nostr keys to DNS\-based internet identifiers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 2
\&    use AnyEvent;
\&    use Net::Nostr::Identifier;
\&
\&    my $pubkey = \*(Aqb0635d6a9851d3aed0cd6c495b282167acf761729078d975fc341b22650b07b9\*(Aq;
\&
\&    # Parse and validate an identifier
\&    my ($local, $domain) = Net::Nostr::Identifier\->parse(\*(Aqbob@example.com\*(Aq);
\&
\&    # Build the well\-known URL
\&    my $url = Net::Nostr::Identifier\->url(\*(Aqbob@example.com\*(Aq);
\&    # https://example.com/.well\-known/nostr.json?name=bob
\&
\&    # Display name (root identifier _@domain shows as domain)
\&    Net::Nostr::Identifier\->display_name(\*(Aqbob@example.com\*(Aq);  # "bob@example.com"
\&    Net::Nostr::Identifier\->display_name(\*(Aq_@bob.com\*(Aq);         # "bob.com"
\&
\&    # Verify a nostr.json response
\&    my $response = { names => { bob => $pubkey } };
\&    if (Net::Nostr::Identifier\->verify_response($response, \*(Aqbob\*(Aq, $pubkey)) {
\&        print "Verified!\en";
\&    }
\&
\&    # Async verification via HTTP (requires an AnyEvent loop)
\&    my $cv = AnyEvent\->condvar;
\&    my $ident = Net::Nostr::Identifier\->new;
\&    $ident\->verify(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqbob@example.com\*(Aq,
\&        pubkey     => $pubkey,
\&        on_success => sub { my ($relays) = @_; print "Verified!\en"; $cv\->send },
\&        on_failure => sub { my ($reason) = @_; warn "Failed: $reason"; $cv\->send },
\&    );
\&    $cv\->recv;
\&
\&    # Async lookup (find pubkey from identifier)
\&    $cv = AnyEvent\->condvar;
\&    $ident\->lookup(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqbob@example.com\*(Aq,
\&        on_success => sub { my ($pubkey, $relays) = @_; $cv\->send },
\&        on_failure => sub { my ($reason) = @_; $cv\->send },
\&    );
\&    $cv\->recv;
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-05 for mapping Nostr public keys to DNS\-based internet
identifiers. An identifier has the form \f(CW\*(C`local\-part@domain\*(C'\fR where the
local\-part uses only characters \f(CW\*(C`a\-z0\-9\-_.\*(C'\fR.
.PP
Clients verify an identifier by fetching
\&\f(CW\*(C`https://<domain>/.well\-known/nostr.json?name=<local\-part>\*(C'\fR
and checking that the returned \f(CW"names"\fR mapping contains the expected
public key.
.PP
The special identifier \f(CW\*(C`_@domain\*(C'\fR is treated as a root identifier and
may be displayed as just the domain.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS parse
.IX Subsection "parse"
.Vb 1
\&    my ($local_part, $domain) = Net::Nostr::Identifier\->parse(\*(Aqbob@example.com\*(Aq);
.Ve
.PP
Splits an identifier into its local\-part and domain. Strictly validates
both parts. Croaks if the identifier is invalid:
.IP \(bu 4
missing or multiple \f(CW\*(C`@\*(C'\fR
.IP \(bu 4
empty local\-part or domain
.IP \(bu 4
local\-part contains characters outside \f(CW\*(C`a\-z0\-9\-_.\*(C'\fR
.IP \(bu 4
domain contains whitespace, \f(CW\*(C`/\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`:\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`?\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`#\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`[\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`]\*(C'\fR, or control characters
.PP
Bracketed IPv6 addresses (e.g. \f(CW\*(C`[::1]\*(C'\fR) are rejected because NIP\-05 is
DNS\-based. Ports are rejected because the spec constructs HTTPS URLs from
the domain directly.
.SS url
.IX Subsection "url"
.Vb 1
\&    my $url = Net::Nostr::Identifier\->url(\*(Aqbob@example.com\*(Aq);
.Ve
.PP
Returns the well\-known URL for verifying the identifier.
.SS display_name
.IX Subsection "display_name"
.Vb 2
\&    my $name = Net::Nostr::Identifier\->display_name(\*(Aqbob@example.com\*(Aq);  # "bob@example.com"
\&    my $root = Net::Nostr::Identifier\->display_name(\*(Aq_@bob.com\*(Aq);        # "bob.com"
.Ve
.PP
Returns the display form of the identifier. Root identifiers (\f(CW\*(C`_@domain\*(C'\fR)
are displayed as just the domain. All other identifiers are returned as\-is.
.SS verify_response
.IX Subsection "verify_response"
.Vb 1
\&    my $ok = Net::Nostr::Identifier\->verify_response($hashref, $local_part, $pubkey);
.Ve
.PP
Returns true if the response hashref maps the given local\-part to the given
pubkey. Keys must be 64\-character lowercase hex (32\-byte public keys).
.SS extract_relays
.IX Subsection "extract_relays"
.Vb 1
\&    my $relays = Net::Nostr::Identifier\->extract_relays($hashref, $pubkey);
.Ve
.PP
Returns an arrayref of relay URLs for the given pubkey, or an empty arrayref
if none are found.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $ident = Net::Nostr::Identifier\->new(%args);
.Ve
.PP
Croaks on unknown arguments.
.IP base_url 4
.IX Item "base_url"
Optional base URL override for testing. When set, HTTP requests go to
this URL instead of \f(CW\*(C`https://<domain>\*(C'\fR.
.SH "INSTANCE METHODS"
.IX Header "INSTANCE METHODS"
.SS verify
.IX Subsection "verify"
.Vb 6
\&    $ident\->verify(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqbob@example.com\*(Aq,
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,
\&        on_success => sub { my ($relays) = @_ },
\&        on_failure => sub { my ($reason) = @_ },
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Asynchronously fetches the well\-known URL and verifies that the identifier
maps to the given pubkey. HTTP redirects are ignored per the spec. Requires
an AnyEvent event loop to be running. Croaks if any required argument is
missing or if \f(CW\*(C`on_success\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`on_failure\*(C'\fR are not CODE refs.
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`on_success\*(C'\fR callback receives an arrayref of relay URLs (may be empty).
The \f(CW\*(C`on_failure\*(C'\fR callback receives an error reason string.
.SS lookup
.IX Subsection "lookup"
.Vb 5
\&    $ident\->lookup(
\&        identifier => \*(Aqbob@example.com\*(Aq,
\&        on_success => sub { my ($pubkey, $relays) = @_ },
\&        on_failure => sub { my ($reason) = @_ },
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Asynchronously fetches the well\-known URL and returns the pubkey associated
with the identifier. HTTP redirects are ignored per the spec. Requires
an AnyEvent event loop to be running. Croaks if any required argument is
missing or if \f(CW\*(C`on_success\*(C'\fR/\f(CW\*(C`on_failure\*(C'\fR are not CODE refs.
.PP
The \f(CW\*(C`on_success\*(C'\fR callback receives the hex pubkey and an arrayref of relay
URLs. The \f(CW\*(C`on_failure\*(C'\fR callback receives an error reason string.
.SH SECURITY
.IX Header "SECURITY"
The \f(CW\*(C`/.well\-known/nostr.json\*(C'\fR endpoint \fBMUST NOT\fR return any HTTP redirects.
This module ignores all HTTP redirects, treating them as verification failures.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.IX Header "SEE ALSO"
NIP\-05 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/05.md>
